#!/usr/bin/env python3
from pwn import *
context.log_level = 'error'

p = process("/challenge/run")

data = p.recvline()
key = int(data.strip().decode().split()[-1])

data = p.recvline()
encrypted_secret = int(data.strip().decode().split()[-1])

decrypted_key = key ^ encrypted_secret

p.sendline(str(decrypted_key).encode())
print(p.recvall().decode())


## 🧑🏾‍🏫 what this challenge teaches u
how to use XOR in python
if data r encrypted, to decrypted them u need the key
in this challenge the goal was: extract the key, extract the encryption value and then XOR them, and send the result
recvline() reads until it finds a \n. the value is bytes
.strip() -> removes \n
.decode() -> converts from bytes in strings
.split() -> splits the string
[-1] -> pick the last value in the array
sendline() -> sends the value to the waiting process
recvall() -> prints the full output

